Join() is Thread class method, if this method invoke, the current Thread stops its
execution and the thread goes into the wait state until the thread on which the join()
method is invoked has achieved it dead/terminate state or wait for the specific time 
mention in join() method argument.



There are 3 overloaded methods in join()
1) public void final join() throws InterruptedException
2) public void final join(long milliseconds) throws InterruptedException
3) public void final join(long milliseconds, nanoseconds) throws InterruptedException
   
